<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1436,370,1956]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis box="[198,327,570,595]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[337,446,570,596]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Holotype</typeStatus>
incomplete, with 43 segments, 
<quantity box="[834,908,570,596]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" unit="mm" value="11.0">11mm</quantity>
long, thorax 
<quantity box="[1074,1135,570,596]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" unit="mm" value="7.0">7mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[1215,1298,570,596]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5mm</quantity>
wide (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="39.[151,255,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[188,1394,154,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-79@39.[161,1446,123,1924]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 10. Loimia minuta (Holotype AMNH 1992): A. Thorax in lateral view. B. Thorax in ventral view. C. Thorax in dorsal view. D,F. Anterior end in lateral view. E. Anterior end in ventral view. G. Bilimbate notochaetae from segments 18. H. Uncinus from segment 5. I. Uncinus from segment 11. J. Uncinus from segment 25. Scale bars: A,B,C,E,F: 1.3mm; D: 1.1mm; G: 0.05mm; H,I,J: 0.02mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316202" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316202/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Figs 10</figureCitation>
A-C). Body brown. Abdomen thinner than thorax, with visible segmentation. Tentacular membrane short, narrow, rounded edge visible on ventral side; eyespots absent; tentacles missing. Upper lip short, narrow, semi-circular, projecting forwards (
<figureCitation box="[571,682,690,716]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="39.[151,255,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[188,1394,154,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-79@39.[161,1446,123,1924]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 10. Loimia minuta (Holotype AMNH 1992): A. Thorax in lateral view. B. Thorax in ventral view. C. Thorax in dorsal view. D,F. Anterior end in lateral view. E. Anterior end in ventral view. G. Bilimbate notochaetae from segments 18. H. Uncinus from segment 5. I. Uncinus from segment 11. J. Uncinus from segment 25. Scale bars: A,B,C,E,F: 1.3mm; D: 1.1mm; G: 0.05mm; H,I,J: 0.02mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316202" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316202/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 10D</figureCitation>
). Lower lip short, swollen and somewhat hidden by segment 1 (
<figureCitation box="[159,269,730,756]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="39.[151,255,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[188,1394,154,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-79@39.[161,1446,123,1924]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 10. Loimia minuta (Holotype AMNH 1992): A. Thorax in lateral view. B. Thorax in ventral view. C. Thorax in dorsal view. D,F. Anterior end in lateral view. E. Anterior end in ventral view. G. Bilimbate notochaetae from segments 18. H. Uncinus from segment 5. I. Uncinus from segment 11. J. Uncinus from segment 25. Scale bars: A,B,C,E,F: 1.3mm; D: 1.1mm; G: 0.05mm; H,I,J: 0.02mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316202" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316202/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 10E</figureCitation>
). First pair of lateral lappets projecting forwards, laterally surrounding tentacular membrane, and lower lip ventrally; second pair with short base, not connected to ventral shield, and with dorsal edge slightly developed, not covering base of branchiae. Sixteen ventral shields from segment 2; first three shields shorter and wider; next 9 shields swollen but decreasing in size posteriorly; last 4 shields divided transversally in two parts; abdomen with mid-ventral longitudinal groove. Nephridial papillae not seen. Notopodial glandular tissue absent. Branchiae branched, spiralled, slightly decreasing in length posteriorly; branchiae on dorsal left side and second right one absent. Notochaetae of two lengths, asymmetrically bilimbate, pointed; chaetae with some longitudinal striations (
<figureCitation box="[493,603,1010,1036]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="39.[151,255,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[188,1394,154,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-79@39.[161,1446,123,1924]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 10. Loimia minuta (Holotype AMNH 1992): A. Thorax in lateral view. B. Thorax in ventral view. C. Thorax in dorsal view. D,F. Anterior end in lateral view. E. Anterior end in ventral view. G. Bilimbate notochaetae from segments 18. H. Uncinus from segment 5. I. Uncinus from segment 11. J. Uncinus from segment 25. Scale bars: A,B,C,E,F: 1.3mm; D: 1.1mm; G: 0.05mm; H,I,J: 0.02mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316202" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316202/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 10G</figureCitation>
). Neuropodia with uncini avicular, with five aligned teeth; uncini from segment 5–10 (
<figureCitation box="[331,438,1050,1076]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="39.[151,255,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[188,1394,154,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-79@39.[161,1446,123,1924]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 10. Loimia minuta (Holotype AMNH 1992): A. Thorax in lateral view. B. Thorax in ventral view. C. Thorax in dorsal view. D,F. Anterior end in lateral view. E. Anterior end in ventral view. G. Bilimbate notochaetae from segments 18. H. Uncinus from segment 5. I. Uncinus from segment 11. J. Uncinus from segment 25. Scale bars: A,B,C,E,F: 1.3mm; D: 1.1mm; G: 0.05mm; H,I,J: 0.02mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316202" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316202/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 10H</figureCitation>
) PP developed, angular; PF absent; Oc long, concave; Cp with 1 vertical row of five teeth, decreasing in size in proportions of 3/4 the above; USr concave; SrP well-developed, rounded and directed anteriorly; LSr concave; AP with AF thin, projected downward; Bs slightly concave. Uncini from segments 11–20 (
<figureCitation box="[360,457,1170,1196]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="39.[151,255,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[188,1394,154,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-79@39.[161,1446,123,1924]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 10. Loimia minuta (Holotype AMNH 1992): A. Thorax in lateral view. B. Thorax in ventral view. C. Thorax in dorsal view. D,F. Anterior end in lateral view. E. Anterior end in ventral view. G. Bilimbate notochaetae from segments 18. H. Uncinus from segment 5. I. Uncinus from segment 11. J. Uncinus from segment 25. Scale bars: A,B,C,E,F: 1.3mm; D: 1.1mm; G: 0.05mm; H,I,J: 0.02mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316202" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316202/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 10I</figureCitation>
) with four aligned teeth; abdominal uncini smaller, with five aligned teeth, distal tooth small (
<figureCitation box="[301,402,1210,1236]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="39.[151,255,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[188,1394,154,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-79@39.[161,1446,123,1924]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 10. Loimia minuta (Holotype AMNH 1992): A. Thorax in lateral view. B. Thorax in ventral view. C. Thorax in dorsal view. D,F. Anterior end in lateral view. E. Anterior end in ventral view. G. Bilimbate notochaetae from segments 18. H. Uncinus from segment 5. I. Uncinus from segment 11. J. Uncinus from segment 25. Scale bars: A,B,C,E,F: 1.3mm; D: 1.1mm; G: 0.05mm; H,I,J: 0.02mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316202" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316202/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 10J</figureCitation>
). Abdominal neuropodia well developed, as swollen lappets with short rows of uncini, straight or semi-curved. Pygidium missing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1436,370,1956]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis box="[198,398,1291,1316]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Staining pattern:</emphasis>
Lateral lappets, first four segments, dorsally, and notopodia, also dorsally, stain deeply. Small longitudinal lateral bands to last two ventral shields and ventral gap between thoracic neuropodia stain lightly. Ventral shields and rest of structures remain pale.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1436,370,1956]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis box="[198,321,1411,1436]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Variation:</emphasis>
Complete specimens from the Mexican 
<taxonomicName authority="Londoño-Mesa, 2009" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" box="[790,910,1410,1436]" genus="Caribbean" pageId="38" pageNumber="4" rank="genus" status="new species, new genus">Caribbean</taxonomicName>
have 102–105 segments, 
<quantity box="[1212,1287,1410,1436]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.2" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" unit="mm" value="62.0">62mm</quantity>
long, thorax 
<quantity box="[151,226,1450,1476]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" unit="mm" value="13.0">13mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[346,406,1450,1476]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" unit="mm" value="3.0">3mm</quantity>
wide, tentacles small, smooth, posterior ventral shields trisected, and pygidium with 6 long digitate papillae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1436,370,1956]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis box="[198,337,1531,1556]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Discussion:</emphasis>
This species was synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="AMNH" authorityYear="1265" box="[782,963,1531,1556]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Loimia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="medusa">
<emphasis box="[782,963,1531,1556]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Loimia medusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Savigny 
<emphasis box="[1088,1111,1531,1556]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">in</emphasis>
Lamarck, 1822) by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fauvel, P." pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="105 - 155" refId="ref61414" refString="Fauvel, P. (1914) Annelides polychetes de San-Thomee (Golf de Guinee) recueillies par M. Ch. Gravier. Archives de zoologie experimentale et generale, 54, 105 - 155." type="journal article" year="1914">Fauvel (1914)</bibRefCitation>
because of the then current belief in wide (cosmopolitan) distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="AMNH" authorityYear="1265" box="[1081,1200,1571,1596]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Loimia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="medusa">
<emphasis box="[1081,1200,1571,1596]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">L. medusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in warm seas. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartman, O." pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="243 - 310" refId="ref61792" refString="Hartman, O. (1956) Polychaetous annelids erected by Treadwell, 1891 - 1948, together with a brief chronology. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 109 (2), 243 - 310." type="journal article" year="1956">Hartman (1956)</bibRefCitation>
followed this concept since the species apparently matched with Savigny’s description. Nevertheless, some important differences were also found in the uncini of the present material, additional to those presented by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hutchings, P. A. &amp; Glasby, C. J." box="[311,646,1690,1716]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="149 - 155" refId="ref62622" refString="Hutchings, P. A. &amp; Glasby, C. J. (1995) Description of the widely reported terebellid polychaetes Loimia medusa (Savigny) and Amphitrite rubra (Risso). Mitteilungen der Zooologisches Staatinstitut und zoologisches Museum, Hamburg, 92, 149 - 155." type="journal article" year="1995">Hutchings &amp; Glasby (1995)</bibRefCitation>
; 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Treadwell" authorityYear="1929" box="[660,773,1691,1716]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Loimia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis box="[660,773,1691,1716]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">L. minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has anterior thoracic uncini with 5 teeth, posterior thoracic uncini with 4 teeth and abdominal uncini with 5 teeth, all uncini with thin AF in this species, while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="AMNH" authorityYear="1265" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Loimia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="medusa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">L. medusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has posterior thoracic uncini and abdominal ones with 4 teeth. On the other hand, 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Verrill" authorityYear="1900" box="[1209,1388,1771,1796]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Loimia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bermudensis">
<emphasis box="[1209,1388,1771,1796]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">L. bermudensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a similar species too, but it differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Treadwell" authorityYear="1929" box="[597,709,1811,1836]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Loimia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis box="[597,709,1811,1836]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">L. minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having all uncini with 5 teeth. Thus, according to this character, it is a distinct species and should be regarded as valid.
</paragraph>
